string.name: Settings_Accessibility_preferred_hand_reverse_desc
string.value:
After switching the direction of single hand optimization, layouts would adjust their display accordingly. 

For example, homepage shortcuts, settings menu, tabs and bookmarks panel would switch their positions for a easier access.

If you want to adjust further based on this, you could toggle:

string.name: Settings_Accessibility_preferred_hand_reverse_tabs_panel
string.value: Reverse tabs & vertical bookmarks panel position

string.name: Settings_experience_history_index_desc
string.value:
Indexing is a technology that accelerates searching by pre-reading data and analyzing them. 

Indexing history often needs an amount of time and space but this is mostly worthy. 

Hit the button below to force rebuild all indices:

Progress would be shown in 󰁡 More Panel!

string.value:
This is space taken up by the history index files. 

Too see more about history indexing, go check out 'History' column!

string.name: Settings_manage_cookies_desc_1
string.value: Cookies are a series of cached data stored in local storage either temporarily or permanently, here in this app, encrypted.

string.value: They remember your accounts, your passwords, your login statuses... Plenty of things.
